Defendant Ted T Spakowski in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Kelly Pingel appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to the charge. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9  YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  -   4 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:   5 years

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s and drug tests ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Ken G. & Cindy G. (victim)
 *DNA sample if not already provided.
 
RESTITUTION:  $2500.00  (already paid)

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 12 months, 9 months huber and the last 3 months STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours. 
Defendant given 275 days credit already served. Sentence to report on 04/18/2016 by 6 pm.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
